 ", "prefix": "on Patreon, a patronage website.", "exact": " “Exposure is not always worthwhile,” says Ms Rose. “But exposure plus getting paid anyway? I won’t complain.”", "type": "TextQuoteSelector"}]}]}, {"created": "2019-02-01T04:19:38.538428+00:00", "text": "A dilemma we're currently facing as we try and decide how best to monetize our projects. In book publishing we kind of take for granted the fact the only model of commercialized publishing is to have readers pay for the full content with maybe just the exception of the first one or two chapters used for promotional purposes. It's a little different for independent publishers, though. I know of one series that got immensely popular when the author posted her first book for free and then made fans pay for the next two books (I believe all three were posted simultaneously, so that helps). It's just interesting thinking about what different models exist ", "tags": [], "updated": "2019-02-01T04:19:38.538428+00:00", "id": "luhMviXYEemf5BPUIGDYjQ", "uri": "https://www.economist.com/christmas-specials/2018/12/18/patreon-kickstarter-and-the-new-patrons-of-the-arts", "permissions": {"delete": ["acct:ajelly@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:ajelly@hypothes.is"], "read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:ajelly@hypothes.is"]}, "user_info": {"display_name": null}, "links": {"incontext": "https://hyp.is/luhMviXYEemf5BPUIGDYjQ/www.economist.com/christmas-specials/2018/12/18/patreon-kickstarter-and-the-new-patrons-of-the-arts", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/luhMviXYEemf5BPUIGDYjQ", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/luhMviXYEemf5BPUIGDYjQ"}, "user": "acct:ajelly@hypothes.is", "document": {"title": ["Patreon, Kickstarter and the new patrons of the arts"]}, "group": "__world__", "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "target": [{"source": "https://www.economist.com/christmas-specials/2018/12/18/patreon-kickstarter-and-the-new-patrons-of-the-arts", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "va